What a perfect breakfast looks like ! Palappam, paneer roast and coconut milk. Recipe for palappam: (This is slightly different from the usual recipe because I've not used soda and yeast) 1. Soak one cup raw rice and one cup idli rice for 6 hrs. Separately soak 6 tbsp urad dal and 1 tsp fenugreek for 6 hrs. 2. To a mixer, add the dal, fenugreek and a handful of coconut. Add lil water and blend it into a smooth thin batter. Then add the rice and blend the batter all together by adding water and salt. 3. Let it ferment for 8-10 hrs. You can make regular hoppers or flat griddle dosas. Recipe for coconut milk: 1. Add 1 cardamom, 3 tbsp sugar and one cup chopped coconut to a mixer. 2. Grind it and then add 3/4 cup water to extract the thick coconut milk. Done! Enjoy! â¤ . . .
